docs.abstract: Companies like Delta are caught between Democrats focused on social justice and populist Republicans. They face major political consequences no matter what they do.
docs.snippet: Companies like Delta are caught between Democrats focused on social justice and populist Republicans. They face major political consequences no matter what they do.
docs.lead_paragraph: On March 11, Delta Air Lines dedicated a building at its Atlanta headquarters to Andrew Young, the civil rights leader and former mayor. At the ceremony, Mr. Young spoke of the restrictive voting rights bill that Republicans were rushing through the Georgia state legislature. Then, after the speeches, Mr. Young’s daughter, Andrea, a prominent activist herself, cornered Delta’s chief executive, Ed Bastian.

headline.main: Inside Corporate America’s Frantic Response to the Georgia Voting Law
headline.print_headline: Voting Limits Raise Pressure On Companies
